  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to ValaDoc </title>

    <para>
      The <application>Vala Docs</application> is a documentation generator for generating API documentation 
      from Vala source code based on libvala. 
    </para>

    &lfs75_checked;

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Package Information</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&valadoc-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (FTP): <ulink url="&valadoc-download-ftp;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download MD5 sum: &valadoc-md5sum;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download size: &valadoc-size;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Estimated disk space required: &valadoc-buildsize;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Estimated build time: &valadoc-time;
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Vala Docs Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <xref linkend="libgee"/>,
      <xref linkend="unzip"/>,  (to extract source)
      <xref linkend="gdk-pixbuf"/>, and
      <xref linkend ="graphviz"/>
    </para>

    <para condition="html" role="usernotes">User Notes:
      <ulink url="&blfs-wiki;/valadoc"/>
    </para>
  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Vala Docs</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>Vala Docs</application> by running
      the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package does not come with a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

